DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(81)90119-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407681901196
AB  - This paper develops the maximum likelihood procedure to estimate the appropriate functional form in regression models with heteroskedastic errors. The analysis can then enable us to separate out the influence of non-linearity in an estimate of the transformation parameter from the influence of stabilizing the error variance. Illustrative examples have been used to show that estimation and tests for functional form and heteroskedasticity can and should be jointly considered.
ER  - 

